<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-21T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-21T13:00:00-05:00" n="719" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d719">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">102.1/4–1749: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-21T13:00:00-05:00">April 21,
                                1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>703. For Parker from Treasury. Reurtel 1215<note n="59" xml:id="d719fn59">April 17, 3 p. m., <ref target="#pg_759">p. 759</ref>.</note> FRBNY
                        advised April 21 sell 100,000 ounces gold to Chicenbank. Received Toeca
                            1345<note n="60" xml:id="d719fn60">April 13, not printed.</note> advise
                        ChiGovt informally and orally that it may rely upon availability gold for
                        future purchases its Central Bank to replenish outlays for purchase tin for
                        delivery under existing arrangements R.F.C. Advise Green[e].<note n="61" xml:id="d719fn61">George H. Greene, Consultant, ECA China
                            Mission.</note> State and ECA concur all above. [Treasury.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>